Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.78,0:02:29.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,2058 A.D.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.53,0:02:34.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Humanity begins to take its first leap into space.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.94,0:02:38.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,An almost unbelievable plan, which would be its first step
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.97,0:02:41.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,toward interstellar travel, was conceived.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.85,0:03:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This project for expansion into outer space \Nwill most likely be repeated several times.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.03,0:03:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope that at least one of them succeeds.{We hope for at least one of them succeeding.}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.58,0:03:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank you two for your cooperation\Nwith this program, Mr. and Mrs. Robinson. {I know you can refer to a couple by just the husband but that feels very old-fashioned. This is inspired by 50s Sci-Fi but I don't think we need to go that far.}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it on the screen. {Onscreen.}{スクリーンを}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.68,0:03:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,With our present technology, \Nmanned interstellar spaceflight is but a dream,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.61,0:03:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,incurring truly astronomical costs.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.85,0:03:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we have developed\N a method of traveling using comets.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.70,0:03:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Abundant energy sources, such as water and deuterium, can be taken directly from the core.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.60,0:03:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We have named this comet "Ozma III". {3 -> III because of manga and likely original inspiration, Project Ozma, a SETI experiment}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.68,0:03:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we will use\N the comet itself as a spaceship.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.14,0:03:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a natural interstellar spaceship, you see.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.88,0:03:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there is a fatal problem.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.47,0:03:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Space is vast.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.87,0:04:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you traveled with Ozma III
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.03,0:04:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at a speed of 80 kilometers a second, \Nhow much time do you think it would take
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.48,0:04:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to travel to Alpha Centauri, \Nthe star closest to our solar system?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.55,0:04:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A staggering 16,000 years.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.09,0:04:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take over 50,000 years \Nto cover the distance of 10 light years.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.85,0:04:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, enormous acceleration is absolutely needed.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.28,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, after we've mined its resources, \Nwe will explode the comet's core.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.36,0:04:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of the blast will accelerate\N the ship to 10,000 kilometers a second.{The energy of the blast will propel the ship \Nto the speeds of 10,000 kilometers a second.}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.78,0:04:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the human body is unable \Nto withstand this tremendous{terrible} acceleration.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.90,0:04:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The only things that could survive it are machines\Nand frozen sperm and eggs.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.76,0:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, life will truly begin with a journey.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.33,0:04:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Mr. and Mrs. Robinson, \NI hope you don't misunderstand us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.28,0:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not playing God with life. {lit: playing with life like a toy}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.20,0:05:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it misses...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.75,0:05:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there are no planets that can support life, \Nwhat will happen to these...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.61,0:05:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,children of ours?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.91,0:05:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They will return to nothingness.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it, Mrs. Robinson.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.91,0:05:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, in that case, the ship will be permanently suspended, at the computer's discretion.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.77,0:05:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The defreezing system for the eggs and sperm \Nwill never activate, and nothing will be born.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.88,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These are {\i1}our{\i0} children.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.55,0:06:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If they {\i1}do{\i0} get born...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.85,0:06:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be all alone,\N out in the far reaches of space.{they'll be all alone on the other side of space.} {lit: opposing end of the cosmos - this sentence is both factually and semantically wrong in english, since they're only flying between two relatively close stars, so "cosmos" here is only this distance between Earth and Ozma, and they mean "the other side of this distance" but that's a mouthful in english and I couldn't think of anything better so I kept "other side of space" from kanjisub translation; it's the same for all instances of this wording used in the OVA}{宇宙の彼方, the kanata can be taken poetically as meaning far away, beyond anyone's grasp. So just go with that.}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.20,0:06:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.94,0:06:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't do anything about it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.07,0:06:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, please.{Come this way.}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.77,0:06:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{We'll}We'd like to show you one more result \Nof your cooperation with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.90,0:06:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hannah... bear a child.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.16,0:06:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Our child.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.42,0:06:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make ourselves a family too,\N here on Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.26,0:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what is it? A boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.60,0:07:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a boy. See, it's got one!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.12,0:07:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me hold it, Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.44,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Me next!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.46,0:07:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the 23rd one, huh, Dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.27,0:07:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you name him?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.23,0:07:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Joachim. {the English translation of the manga changes this to Johann but the JP manga has Joachim too.}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.42,0:07:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and I decided.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.33,0:07:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What a weird name.{That's a funny name.}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.50,0:07:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We should give him a better name. \NLet's vote on it.{I think they could name it something else. \NLet's take the majority vote.}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.13,0:07:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Joachim, these are your big brothers and sisters. \NYou must be surprised to have so many!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.12,0:07:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, let me hold him! {papa}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.20,0:07:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Don't drop him.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.47,0:07:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.19,0:07:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now. We need to give him some milk.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.69,0:07:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, let me give him milk!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.27,0:08:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.57,0:08:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an air leak.{An air leak. Nothing major. I'll go fix it.}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.78,0:08:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing major. I'll go fix it.{An air leak. Nothing major. I'll go fix it.}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.69,0:08:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.83,0:08:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I'll go on ahead!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.42,0:08:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not fair, Chris! \NYou did it last time! I'll go too!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.98,0:08:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Tau Ceti{ of the Whale Constellation}, huh? {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cetus_(constellation)}{don't need to mention the constellation separately IMO, the Ceti tells you that and the JP just works around not natively having the Latin names we use in English, since Beyer designations and Western constellations are relatively new to them. You'd also phrase it a bit differently if you were to include it though. The constellation is generally called Cetus even in English so it doesn't make much sense to put Whale, even if that would be the translation. You'd also say a star is "in" a constellation, not "of".}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.69,0:08:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what they called that star on Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.74,0:08:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Its size and brightness are a lot like the Sun's.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.65,0:08:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad named the second planet\N of this system Ozma.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.20,0:09:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the name of the comet\N that brought us here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.41,0:09:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, check the angle \Non the solar panel while you're at it, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.35,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's fiddled with the console, it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.02,0:09:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.85,0:09:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, huh? Oh well.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.60,0:09:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, can we really live on Ozma?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.21,0:09:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.05,0:09:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer decided that.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.59,0:09:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer found this planet and is investigating it right now, while we're in orbit.{It was found, and is being investigated now, \Nas we orbit it, by the omnipotent computer.}{"omnipotent"? This word means all-powerful. I struggle to see how it applies to the ship computer. It holds some power over its passengers, but that's not omnipotence. Reserve it for gods and the like.}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.96,0:09:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. While that was happening,\N you were born and have grown up so much.{Yep. While that happened, you were born, \Nand have grown up so much.}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.59,0:09:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.36,0:10:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.44,0:10:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Ozma look like Earth, Mom?{Is Ozma like Earth, mom?}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.99,0:10:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was big and blue like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.70,0:10:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth Mom knows \Nis from a long time ago, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.50,0:10:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the Earth far away?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.71,0:10:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you and Dad want to go home?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.61,0:11:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Dad have you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.88,0:11:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have Ozma.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.52,0:11:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember this well.{Remember this well, that star is the Sun.}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.95,0:11:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That star is the Sun.{Remember this well, that star is the Sun.}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.64,0:11:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Since ancient times, people on Earth\N have looked at the stars like this and said:
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.68,0:11:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'd like to go to that star someday.\NI wonder if I'll be able to someday."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.49,0:11:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And while they thought that, \Npeople lived and died,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.47,0:11:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and now, we're the first \Nto go to one of those stars.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.94,0:11:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand, {Marlene}Maureen? {was: morgan - but later she is addressed more audibly as "maurin" - could also be molly ig?; it's "ann" in the book translation (volume #1 page 79) and I have no idea why they changed it}{モーリン in the credits; Maureen is an Anglicized form of an Irish name that traces back to Maria and ultimately Miriam. The JP manga has Ann too, so they just changed it ig.}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.50,0:11:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. {yeah the timing is off but I'm 90% sure it should be after the scene change anyway.}
Dialogue: 8,0:11:53.01,0:11:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Chris, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.21,0:11:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same disease that hit Harry.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.99,0:12:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,His fever is so high.{He's running a bad fever... out of the blue!} {ngl this reads like ass, bravo kanjisub}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.75,0:12:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so suddenly?{He's running a bad fever... out of the blue!} {ngl the original reads like ass, bravo kanjisub}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.04,0:12:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move him to the medical capsule.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.70,0:12:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good, Dad! The capsule's broken!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:12.24,0:12:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then get him an oxygen mask, quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.04,0:12:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris... Chris, hang on!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.36,0:12:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Toby, get the cardiotonics. \NThey're on that shelf! Hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.29,0:13:36.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Happy birthday to you\NHappy birthday to you
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.26,0:13:40.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Happy birthday, dear Maureen
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.88,0:13:45.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Happy birthday to you
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.01,0:13:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The day we land on Ozma is near.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.36,0:13:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a big birthday party.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.60,0:13:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This will probably be our last... {Probably, this will be your last...}{the last time their robot "parents" celebrate with them. JP is お前たちと最後の, last time with you}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.61,0:13:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Last?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.39,0:13:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, I mean the last party on this ship.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.77,0:14:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those of you who were born this month, \NToby, Maureen, Mark, blow it out together. {in book: TOBY, MARK, AND ELLEN--}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.27,0:14:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, your presents.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.08,0:14:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wheat seeds for the boys \Nand sunflowers for Maureen.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.04,0:14:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Grow them with care.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.78,0:14:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.77,0:14:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this is good!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.30,0:16:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's wind!{It's the wind!}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.67,0:16:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so many smells!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.20,0:16:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, so much space! \NThis place is huge!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.30,0:16:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky and the water are so blue!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.53,0:16:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, Dad, come here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.93,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing... This place is amazing!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.19,0:16:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see mountains!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.37,0:16:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They go on forever!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.31,0:16:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful, Joachim.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.35,0:16:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you there. \NQuick!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.79,0:16:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.82,0:16:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Go with them, Joachim.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.90,0:16:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This world belongs to you kids.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.83,0:17:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more we can teach you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.69,0:17:40.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Radio transmissions{waves} carrying the report that 22 children
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.17,0:17:43.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,had landed on planet Ozma\N in the Tau Ceti system,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.48,0:17:50.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{of the Whale Constellation,}11.9 light years from the solar system,\N later reached Earth. {same as previously, either leave out entirely or do "in [the constellation] Cetus"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.22,0:17:57.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But those involved in the plan\N would never receive this report.{But those who sent them there could never receive it.}{lit: those involved in the plan didn't know}{why rewrite it in a way that makes it easy to misunderstand? "those who sent them there" the radio waves? the children?}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.19,0:18:04.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It had been 375 years \Nsince the spaceship left the solar system.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.36,0:18:44.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Humanity's greatest discovery\N in the latter half of the 21st century{The greatest discovery \Nof the latter half of the 21st century}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.94,0:18:50.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was uncovering the true nature of\N the tenth planet of the Solar System.{was the existence of a 10th planet \Nin the Solar System.} {pulling on the manga as well as the JP here: 惑星の正体が明らかになったこと - Lucifer is officially discovered in the 1990s but only much later, in Chapter 8 (7 in EN), they actually travel there and discover that it's composed of antimatter.}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.83,0:18:59.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly, this dark super giant, named Lucifer, \Nwas composed of antimatter.{Surprisingly, this super-large star, named Lucifer, \Nwas made of anti-matter.}{I'd like to avoid star/planet here since the JP words are ambiguous, and switching between star and planet would be confusing.}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.31,0:19:06.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Harnessing it would provide access\N to truly unlimited amounts of energy. {If that could be used, it would allow access to truly unlimited amounts of energy.}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.48,0:19:13.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Space Age entered a new stage \Nwhich humanity had never anticipated.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.23,0:19:25.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the cutting edge of physics was on the verge of completing a theory
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.99,0:19:31.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of hyperspace travel based on\N the rotational confinement of micro black holes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.25,0:19:43.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This combination of infinite energy\N and the latest technology{The fusion of infinite energy \Nand the latest technology}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.57,0:19:49.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,introduced an age in which interstellar flights of tens of light years could be completed in an instant.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.26,0:19:55.48,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,The curtain had suddenly opened\N on humanity's great expansion into space.{Humanity's great expansion into space \Nhad suddenly sprang forth.}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.79,0:20:22.96,Top,,0,0,0,,This ship will now transition\N into hyperspace travel.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.90,0:21:45.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,So this is the kind of planet... \Nthe kind of world you're aiming for?{Is this the planet... is this the world that we're after?} {so this line is a double entendre,both here and in the manga, where it's just …こんな星にー - the ones really aiming for this planet are his unborn siblings on the spaceship. But how do you convey that without giving away the twist of this chapter? And I do think the "kind of" is important here because it's}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.46,0:22:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, let's set the boundaries\N around here, Miller.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:21.96,0:22:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll blast this stony bedrock\N and turn it into soil.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:25.96,0:22:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We need as much organic material\N in the atmosphere and crust as possible.{Plant as much organic material \Ninto the atmosphere and the crust as we can.}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.10,0:22:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the enhanced microbes? {enhanced as in they've been genetically modified to be better}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:30.98,0:22:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're multiplying well.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.82,0:22:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the soil's ready, \NI want to distribute the plant life.{wtf is that verb, also he uses 植物種子 which implies seeds specifically}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.49,0:22:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Speed it up as much as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:40.01,0:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger, Adam.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:20.30,0:23:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an additive with organic matter \Nthat also serves as a fertilizer.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.59,0:23:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This planet is nothing but solid rock.{This planet is made entirely of soapstone.}{I can't hear 石けん石 anywhere here, but I also can't figure it out. My best guess is something to do with 珪質, so siliceous rock (which is also 90% of all rock on Earth). Thus I'd rather keep it vague like kanjisub did.}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.16,0:23:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Just smashing the stones and spreading seeds\N around won't be enough to grow anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.95,0:23:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's add that area over there\N to the development.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.57,0:23:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez, what a depressing planet.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.41,0:24:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the development's far behind schedule. \NWho knows when we'll be able to go back to Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.72,0:24:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Robinson Foundation's pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:06.63,0:24:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They say the entire Foundation\N is focused on this project.{They've shifted their whole company\Naround this development.}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.67,0:24:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll probably start advertising it\N once the environment's mostly set up.{When the environment is mostly set up, \Nthey'll probably make an announcement.} {is how I interpret "PR" in this context}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.59,0:24:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"Build a villa on a green planet," or something.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.66,0:24:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at a hundred times the normal price.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:25.76,0:24:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Adam!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:27.26,0:24:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying this as your financial advisor!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:30.90,0:24:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Robinson Space Foundation's capital has its limits!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:34.49,0:24:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you continue this large-scale construction,\Nthe Foundation will go bankrupt!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:39.05,0:24:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilford, no matter how often\N you say that to me,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.62,0:24:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to abandon the project midstream.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.44,0:24:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Adam!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:51.12,0:24:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father's involvement in a top-secret\N Space Agency project is what allowed him{Your father's cooperation in the Space Bureau's secret plan was the beginning of his involvement with the space industry.}{宇宙局 means space agency even if 局 means bureau/department on its own, and it's used a few times in the manga but the only instance I found (chapter 9, 8 in EN) while looking through it rn was mistranslated in the English version to Allied Space Bureau (which appears in chapter 8 (7 in EN) as 宇宙省 in JP - more literally Space Ministry, but the sign on the door said ASB)}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:57.39,0:25:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to establish himself in the space industry.{Your father's cooperation in the Space Bureau's secret plan was the beginning of his involvement with the space industry.}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.57,0:25:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he amassed his enormous wealth in the Lucifer Development Project
Dialogue: 10,0:25:04.91,0:25:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was about your age.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:08.97,0:25:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, in my position, I cannot let this lie.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:15.74,0:25:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll become an issue that we'll have\N to deal with once we return to Earth.{When we return to Earth, \NI'll have to bring it up with the foundation.} {lit: as a foundation, we'll have a problem}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:20.19,0:25:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodnight.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.42,0:25:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This lake is the furthest thing along in the project.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:45.96,0:25:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost done with the landscaping,\N and our aquatic cultures are developing well.{The terrain preparation is almost completed, \Nand the aquatic life breeding is continuing well.}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:50.77,0:25:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's left to do is to fill it\N with water from the canal.{All that remains is to draw the water from the canal.}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.87,0:26:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure this will be wonderful to look at.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:02.18,0:26:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we finish this, \Nmaybe we should take the day off?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:50.79,0:26:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What an awful rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:52.49,0:26:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never see this kind of downpour on Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:58.57,0:27:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Our atmospheric terraforming may have\N disrupted the planet's weather patterns.{We may have broken the weather balance \Nwith our atmospheric terraforming.}{balance feels like the wrong word here, a bit of a false friend ig. Also "atmospheric terraforming" sounds dumb but idt there's a better way to put that since terraforming explicitly includes altering the atmosphere}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:06.61,0:27:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Adam.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.61,0:27:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you're committed to this project.{I understand your troubles, \Nbut as your science advisor, let me tell you this.} {this gap is like 1.7 secs, really should split it.}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.92,0:27:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But as your science advisor,\N let me tell you this much.{I understand your troubles, \Nbut as your science advisor, let me tell you this.}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:15.38,0:27:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is another planet. \NIt's not Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:18.49,0:27:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The changes we make to the environment\N will be strictly temporary.{Changing the environment \Nis merely a stopgap measure.}{stopgap doesn't fit at all here, a stopgap fills a gap, there is no gap to another similar project here.}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:22.44,0:27:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't expect them to last.{You shouldn't expect these changes to last.}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.01,0:27:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In 600 years, everything will return to its original state.{In 600 years it will return to its original state.}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:29.53,0:27:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more than enough time, Miller.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:31.52,0:27:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not the ones who need to think \Nabout 600 years from now.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:49.88,0:27:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! What?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:50.88,0:27:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alarm! {????????? maybe "Chief!"}{the timing in this section is atrocious but it's not like I can make out stuff}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:51.85,0:27:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:10.26,0:28:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?! What happened?!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.82,0:28:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The lake overflowed!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:18.82,0:28:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill up that valley \Nand change the flow of the water! {not sure how they're supposed to do that posthaste and how it's going to change the waterflow}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:30.83,0:28:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible! \NThere's not nearly enough time! {yea exactly}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.10,0:28:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we do nothing, \Nthe plants will be destroyed! {as in flora}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:39.26,0:28:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Working in this rain is dangerous!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:42.19,0:28:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to fall back now!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.68,0:28:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If the water comes \Nbefore we dam it up, we're dead!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:46.63,0:28:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we abandon the plants \Nthat have finally budded, it'll all be for naught!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:50.32,0:28:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the water even if you have \Nto use every man we have!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:30.99,0:29:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mess.{It's awful.}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:32.72,0:29:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it was all for naught.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:36.91,0:29:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, send us back to Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:40.78,0:29:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ever want to do \Nsomething that dangerous again.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.71,0:29:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We should leave as soon as we can.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:45.70,0:29:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the Foundation be able to survive this? {meaning won't it go bankrupt from losing all this equipment}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:49.21,0:29:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:50.46,0:29:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A ship carrying equipment will arrive soon.{A depot ship carrying equipment \Nwill be here soon.} {"depot ship" is just taking the first definition from jisho isn't it. I don't think they're talking about a military ship like that. Not that any possible meaning of bosen makes sense here. That one is the big thing in orbit (and on the poster). I vote to leave it vague.}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:53.46,0:29:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who wish to return on it may do so. \NThank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:45.31,0:30:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:46.61,0:30:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of the rest here.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:43.09,0:32:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:45.01,0:32:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In 300 years, you will reach this planet.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:49.57,0:32:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I leave this message for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:54.26,0:33:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years ago, humanity's desire and rush \Ntoward space led to a desperate plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:05.39,0:33:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, they put frozen human sperm and eggs\N on a spaceship and sent it to this planet.{Well,} {putting frozen human sperm and eggs on a spaceship, \Nand sending them to this planet.}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:15.96,0:33:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones who provided them\N were the Robinsons.{The Robinsons were the ones who provided them.}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:19.92,0:33:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:25.74,0:33:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:27.76,0:33:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My as yet unborn brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 10,0:33:32.62,0:33:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,heading here at full speed\N from the depths of space...{heading here at full speed from the other side of space...}{真っしぐら = at full speed, headlong, precipitately.}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:02.05,0:34:04.01,Top,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters. {not sure if these need to be top}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:04.01,0:34:08.72,Top,,0,0,0,,My as yet unborn brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:08.72,0:34:11.77,Top,,0,0,0,,heading here at full speed\N from the depths of space...{heading here at full speed from the other side of space...}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.39,0:34:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, thanks to plant photosynthesis,\N the atmosphere's oxygen content will increase.{Eventually the photosynthesis in plants will provide\Nmore oxygen to the planet's atmosphere.} {lit: plant respiration}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:22.39,0:34:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't recover that ship halfway through its journey?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:26.41,0:34:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 11.9 light years from here to Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:30.47,0:34:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Only God knows where they are now.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.50,0:34:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the will of my late parents. {? does he call them dead because they've departed on that ship? were those only their robo copies or something that departed and brought the kids to ozma while the actual robinsons just died of old age? god knows}{they couldn't have made it much more obvious that the ones on the ship were robots without literally saying it. And yeah, they probably died at some point in the 50 years between these two stories.}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:40.22,0:34:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The funds of the Foundation\N were to be used for this purpose.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:31.39,0:35:33.20,Top,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:33.20,0:35:37.89,Top,,0,0,0,,My as yet unborn brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 10,0:35:37.89,0:35:40.74,Top,,0,0,0,,heading here at full speed\N from the depths of space...{My yet unborn brothers and sisters, heading here\Nat full speed from the other side of space...}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:41.43,0:35:46.44,Top,,0,0,0,,Please, take this small gift from Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:46.44,0:35:55.61,Top,,0,0,0,,And never forget that your mother, \Nyour father, and I... are with you...{And never forget...} {Your Mother, your Father, and I, are with you...}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:33.53,0:36:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the colonies established throughout the Galaxy
Dialogue: 10,0:36:38.26,0:36:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,have been abandoned due to epidemics, \Nwars, and natural disasters.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:45.10,0:36:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The massive investments \Nhave gone completely to waste.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:50.45,0:36:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of sending any more men into space,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:54.45,0:36:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we should address the more pressing issue
Dialogue: 10,0:36:56.91,0:37:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of sustaining the lives of the 7.2 billion people here on Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:01.94,0:37:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:03.31,0:37:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we must strive for the utmost optimization of all necessary management and streamlining efforts. {/rationalization}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:10.53,0:37:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Space Age is in the past now.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:27.16,0:38:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:28.67,0:38:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:29.56,0:38:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:30.45,0:38:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Karen!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:35.87,0:38:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:36.28,0:38:37.68,Overlap,,0,0,0,,{It's huge!}{????}Way to go, Toby! {いいぞトビー}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:37.23,0:38:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:39.97,0:38:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!{Way to go!} {because the "way to go" fits the iizo better}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:41.88,0:38:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Joachim, come back! \NIt's dinnertime!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:44.82,0:38:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! There are scary bugs over there! {イボイボムシ}{these names seem to be made up children's language for whatever animals. They're mentioned in the manga but you don't see what either of them are. For this one I could find イボムシ, which is a folk name for a type of mantis that was supposed to heal warts? The term used here can be taken to mean "warty insect" or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:47.88,0:38:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to find cricky-crickies, really big ones!{I'm going to find mushrooms!}{????}{コロキリ}{Big ones!}{so my guess here is that this is supposed to be derived from コロギス, which is the Japanese cricket.}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:56.92,0:38:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:23.79,0:39:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's people!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:25.31,0:39:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, people!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:37.40,0:39:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:47.45,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Joachim, that's not Dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:57.79,0:40:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can’t breathe air this fresh\N on Earth anymore, can you?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:03.45,0:40:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:05.00,0:40:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth? He said Earth...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:11.09,0:40:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? They came from Earth? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:13.65,0:40:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,From Earth?! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:15.20,0:40:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:17.38,0:40:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I wanna go there too!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:20.23,0:40:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what it's like... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:23.01,0:40:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell us!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:25.54,0:40:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:34.88,0:40:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our little brother built it \Nso that we could always gaze at it. {otoutotach referring to adam robinson and his foundation}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:45.67,0:40:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Spain,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:46.98,0:40:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Finland,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:47.85,0:40:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,USA,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:48.93,0:40:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Corsica! {how is that even on their map}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:49.98,0:40:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a country, Joseph!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:52.42,0:40:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell us about the Earth, mister.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:55.30,0:40:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's gotta be a lot of people! {\i1}A lot{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:59.46,0:41:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it bigger than Ozma?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:01.30,0:41:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the sky blue? And the water?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:03.39,0:41:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are animals, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:04.78,0:41:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's it like? {????? }
Dialogue: 10,0:41:05.78,0:41:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there fish?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:06.65,0:41:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What about fish?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:08.62,0:41:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not really that different.\NThis planet was terraformed to be like Earth.{Well, it's not really that different. \NThis planet was terraformed after Earth.} {meaning "to resemble earth"}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.34,0:41:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But now...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:18.27,0:41:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ellen, bring some water.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:20.13,0:41:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:22.45,0:41:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll pass soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:27.66,0:41:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:29.22,0:41:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Karen Robinson.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:30.99,0:41:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the eldest.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:37.88,0:41:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We should've disembarked fully\N right from the start!{We should have just gone ahead \Nand landed right from the start.} {by force - probably means adam made them wander around or soemthing?}{So they want to settle on this planet and the captain first wants to talk to the children who "own" the planet while his subordinates are willing to just force their way in. They only landed with a small shuttle after all.}{lit. is "Right from the start forcefully landing/disembarking would have been better"or smth}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:41.58,0:41:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the captain hesitating about?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:43.34,0:41:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry about those kids.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:46.94,0:41:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If we need to, we'll use force.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:29.79,0:42:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Smith, try to look for a possible \Nsettlement area while they're gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:34.00,0:42:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As large a one as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:35.20,0:42:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:50.58,0:42:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They've split up.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:52.52,0:42:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Harry, you follow him.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:55.29,0:42:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wanted to ride the shuttle\N with everyone else...
Dialogue: 10,0:42:59.18,0:43:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop wasting time and get moving!{Stop standing there and get moving!}
Dialogue: 10,0:43:01.38,0:43:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:29.84,0:43:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're planning something, sister. \NYou can't trust them.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:33.93,0:43:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Or that Captain Adam.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:37.06,0:43:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:38.77,0:43:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There were many settlements made in space.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:42.07,0:43:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There were even planets where tens\N of thousands of people had migrated.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:45.30,0:43:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're gone now. \NAll were abandoned.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:50.14,0:43:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:55.23,0:43:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, I wonder...
Dialogue: 10,0:43:57.31,0:43:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe space was too vast.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:59.70,0:44:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how far we went, it never ended.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:01.98,0:44:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, maybe that vastness\N scared humanity.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:06.08,0:44:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's no reason for us\N to stay on Ozma, is there?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:15.75,0:44:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to return to Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:20.51,0:44:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have that right.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:30.44,0:44:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:32.36,0:44:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:33.57,0:44:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:34.27,0:44:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a spaceship?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:38.09,0:44:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:48.03,0:44:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a starseed!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:49.60,0:44:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A starseed?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:51.20,0:44:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that they were discovered\N around a star in the constellation Orion.{I've heard that they were discovered\Nin the Orion Constellation.} {discovered as if it's a natural thing and not man-made... right.}{they're produced by giant plants, the manga chapter just before this one (19, or 18 in English) is about how Adam encountered one in space and then found their producers on a planet around Betelgeuse (Alpha Orionis). This entire segment is heavily changed from the manga chapter it adapts so this is just one of those retcons.}
Dialogue: 10,0:44:55.41,0:45:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's packed full of plant seeds, wandering through space in search of a place to grow. {again, is that thing doing it on its own, and it just randomly happened to drift by ozma? right...}{in the manga they fire these out at some frequency. The issue I see is that this thing has a solar sail of sorts, and thus should be going way faster than this, at relativistic speeds. The one they encounter in the manga was at 0.7c.}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:04.20,0:45:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they do that? {yes, seeds, they all have decided together that that thing has a mind of its own}{the starseed isn't sentient (at least isn't said to be), so maybe "search" in the previous line is inappropriate, the plants that created it possibly are, since they did figure out this whole orbital launch (via sodium-water reactions) and solar sail tech.}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:06.21,0:45:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows? They make their own offspring\N travel aimlessly through space.{Who knows why do they make their own offspring \Ntravel aimlessly throughout space?}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:12.68,0:45:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe their home planet's\N environment was ruined?{Maybe their home planet's environment \Nmay have been ruined?}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:17.02,0:45:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe...
Dialogue: 10,0:45:19.73,0:45:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they just felt compelled \Nto leave their mark on the Galaxy. {inevitably}{this is still about the plant seeds that somehow made it into space btw}{yup, plants that used a planet-spanning fibre optics network and sodium explosions to create a giant solar sail seed powered by a star on the brink of supernova. Which is arguably less out there than the antimatter planet, and definitely less out there than the FTL drives which violate causality.}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:54.54,0:45:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:56.94,0:45:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're burning down this ugly shack. {eyesore}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:00.61,0:46:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:01.68,0:46:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:04.15,0:46:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us go!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:05.89,0:46:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for your own sake. \NBetter just forget about Earth!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:27.91,0:46:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, this is Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:32.17,0:46:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The aging, decrepit Earth!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:47.70,0:46:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This spaceship will not return to Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:52.57,0:46:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth has changed.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:58.52,0:47:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity wanted to reach out into space.\NIt was an irresistible urge.{Humanity wanted to spread to space. \NIt was a difficult fixation to suppress.}
Dialogue: 10,0:47:04.38,0:47:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,370 years ago, in an era when interstellar travel\Nwas thought totally impossible, {you were sent here.}{this isn't an ellipsis, just a long pause}
Dialogue: 10,0:47:13.97,0:47:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you were a symbol of humanity's dreams\N about space, a source of solace.{You were the symbol of humanity's dreams \Ntowards space, and its salvation.}{so the "solace/salvation" part I'm not exactly sure on. 救い means saving, as in help, or as in saving grace, or as in redemption, or as in solace, or as in salvation (in the religious sense). Here it's probably used in a spiritual manner.}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:02.97,0:48:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That still hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:05.68,0:48:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, ironically, now that all settlements have been lost...{No, ironically, now when \Nall the settlements have been lost...}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:13.70,0:48:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, come. \NThere's something I must have you see.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:10.79,0:49:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away! Get off of this planet!{Get off! Get off of this planet!}
Dialogue: 10,0:49:13.70,0:49:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:49:24.05,0:49:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 10,0:49:47.16,0:49:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to force you \Nto accept those people here.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:58.65,0:50:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This planet...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:02.52,0:50:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,belongs to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:04.50,0:50:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Robinson left it for you and you alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:08.93,0:50:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:13.00,0:50:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Robinson...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:15.74,0:50:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a descendant of the Robinson family too. {kanjisub used "member" here ftr, which works well even though the JP word used here is "descendant"}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:28.57,0:50:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But Adam, we came here as the last colonists, \Nsearching for a new frontier. {dunno what he means by last colonists, probably last resort?}{the Earth government has officially declared that the era of spaceflight is over. They're the last ones, the ones who didn't want to accept that.}{in the manga this all plays out s a bit differently. The previous chapter establishes that there's a last push to discover intelligent alien lifeforms within 500ly of the solar system, and, failing that, to cease all interstellar spaceflight. And the ship he arrives with in Tau Ceti is staffed by a group of "new generation" humans who saved him from his shipwrecking on the Betelgeuse plant planet, and who want to explore the rest of the galaxy with a hyperspace capable starship, for which they tried to kidnap the kids for their old genes. Adam and his right hand man Eagle prevent it and Toby stabs Adam in the end, symbolizing the end of "oldtype" spaceflight, leaving only the children and the new generation guys outside the Earth sphere. But because you can't fit all that context into an OVA (and because it's quite downer) they rewrote it a bunch.}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:35.76,0:50:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't leave here now.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:38.89,0:50:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The children need us too!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:43.71,0:50:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Asimov...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:45.79,0:50:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If the children refuse...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:50.14,0:50:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we will leave.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:52.92,0:50:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the agreement.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:56.65,0:51:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We would take upon us the fate that was laid out\N for these children: become a starseed ourselves...{That is not the fate laid out for these children...}{????} {Now it’s our turn to become a starseed.}{so I've combined these because I'm not sure about the "oima" part where the old break was, and because they're logically connected. The children were starseeds, and now they, as the last colony ship, can take over that mantle should they not be welcome on Ozma.}
Dialogue: 10,0:51:05.77,0:51:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and simply find another planet.{We can always find another planet.}
Dialogue: 10,0:51:09.22,0:51:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam...
Dialogue: 10,0:51:15.42,0:51:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:17.91,0:51:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wanted to meet you kids \Nat least once before I died.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:24.99,0:51:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We kept this planet \Nin our hearts for generations.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:31.37,0:51:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No one ever forgot about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:34.90,0:52:44.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Robinsons gave us life, \Nlove, and the Earth itself. {chikyuu as in the planet, not the ground, so it needs to be capitalized even if it's not actually the planet they're on.}
Dialogue: 10,0:52:45.33,0:52:46.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,Adam...
Dialogue: 10,0:52:47.29,0:52:49.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,Rest in peace in this land.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:29.46,0:53:31.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The history of this family
Dialogue: 10,0:53:31.89,0:53:36.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,mirrored that of the Space Age,\N which had lasted for four centuries.{could be said to be the history of the Space Age, \Nwhich continued for another four centuries.}
Dialogue: 10,0:53:36.90,0:53:41.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Right now, the dreams of humanity\N seem to have changed completely.{Now, the dreams of humanity seem to have come true.} {今、人類の夢は一気変えたかに見える, or something.}{this refers to the end of spaceflight, as the opening narration for this segment already said, humanity no longer reaches for the stars}
Dialogue: 10,0:53:42.60,0:53:48.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But someday, a time will come \Nwhen another generation
Dialogue: 10,0:53:48.13,0:53:55.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,will challenge endless space once again \Nand have the courage to cross it.
